I"“<p>As part of my National Service commitments, I was conscripted into the Singapore Armed Forces.
After completion of 3 months Basic Military Training, and 6 months of commander training in the 
Specialist and Warrant Officers institute I was given the rank of third seargent and was posted 
to an active infantry battalion.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Managed peacetime regimentation, discipline, and training of the Company HQ Platoon (55 men) 
and commanded a Man-Portable Anti-Tank Section (6 men)</li>
  <li>Awarded Best Commander of the Quarter for successfully managing a security threat that arose 
during peacetime military operations at Jurong Island</li>
</ul>
